To compile a file with c++ on raspian

Use latest supported version on raspian.

g++ -std=c++14 hello.cpp -ohello


g++ hello.cpp -ohello // by default uses a older version of compiler

set up alias in ~/.bashrc
alias g++="g++ -std=c++14"

g++ hello.cpp -ohello // will now use later version


c++2a
c++17
c++14 --latest installed version on my raspian
c++11
c++0x


